# One-shot cycle on the first loop() call: feeds the watchdog for 2s (should
# not fire), then stops feeding and sleeps, letting the watchdog wake it after
# roughly the remaining ~250ms of its 500ms timeout.
# See EEPROMTest.timeline's note on normalize_call_whitespace -- matching
# from "(" onward since the space before it doesn't survive the preprocessor.
#
# Trimmed to 2 checkpoints: the real ~2.3s+ first loop() call already
# dominates the cost here, and every event past that only adds another full
# ~1s trivial call (loop() is a no-op after the one-shot "done" flag is set),
# so fewer checkpoints buys real margin without losing coverage.
0.1, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "(should NOT reset)..."
2.6, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "=== done ==="
